  "doc_id": "11230",
  "text": "H2. Extraversion will be positively associated with trust. Innovative software, especially on smartphones, has a high potential to foster social interaction. Extroverted people who are talkative and keen on social interaction with others will see much more benefit and use in getting in touch with such kind of technology than introverted ones who are happy with being on their own. Rosen and Kluemper [CITATION_1] are in line with this argumentation: \"Social networking sites would be another way for extroverts to assert themselves and thus could be considered quite useful (p. 4).\"",
  "correct_citation": {
